The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, January 17, 2004 				 Soft drink tests order
 OUR LEGAL REPORTER																								A division bench of Calcutta High Court, comprising Chief Justice A.K. Mathur and Justice A.K. Bannerjee, on Friday directed the state pollution control board to submit an affidavit within four weeks stating whether it had found cadmium and lead in the soft drink samples it had tested months ago.																								The court passed the order on the basis of a petition filed by environment activist Subhas Dutta, alleging that the board had tested samples of two multinational soft drinks companies and found cadmium and lead in them. But no details had been disclosed since. 																								Dutta also demanded that the court direct soft drink companies to label their bottles with details of the contents.
